{
  "abstract": "Blanchability is ease of test/skin removal and cleaning of the groundnut (Arachis hypogaea L.) kernal\r\nsurgace.  It is atrait of economic importance in processed groundnut food products.  The blanching conditions\r\nof pre-heating temperature of 110 degress celcius for 35 min, with 200 g kernal sample at a blanching time\r\nof 2 min and blanching air pressure of 17.6 psi, which gave satisfactory results, were standardized.  Ten\r\nVirginia bunch large-kernel groundnut varieties grown in 2007 rainy season and 32007/08 postrainy season\r\nat the ICRISAT Centre were evaluated for their blanchability.",
